  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prochnik.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You mean the camps and things like that?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Discussion how?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just, whatever?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The war sort of splits up into two energies for me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One is my [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] exciting experience of it because to be a child and growing up in New York during World War II was very exciting.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's hard to describe now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, it's hard to understand because nothing like that has happened since.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But for a kid, it had a kind of movie-like energy to it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You'd collect scrap metal, and you'd, you know-- and you'd buy war stamps or sell war stamps.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, there was a sense that the good people of the world were fighting the bad people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was the last war where that feeling really existed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that was very, very-- you know, on the war movies, you would see all these films, and you'd walk out of the theater identified with Errol Flynn or Tyrone Power or whoever else, other wonderful Jewish actors [LAUGHS] who were making the movies.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that was-- that, that was very, very exciting.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We-- I, I used to dream of-- I think Woody Allen does that in one of his movies-- but I used to-- and as all kids my age did-- that I would be the one who would spot the Japanese plane flying over New York and become the great hero.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We used to actually get these little booklets that were handed out by Wonder Bread or one of those companies, identifying in silhouette all the enemy planes.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you could go on the roof and be part of like the civil defense thing where you would look through binoculars for enemy planes at night.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
